ActNorthwest Territories Act
SubjectSALT RIVER - Transfer of lands from the Commissioner of the Northwest Territories -
PrecisOrder 1) accepting the transfer of administration and control of land from the Commissioner of the Northwest Territories, 2) setting apart for the use and benefit of the SALT RIVER FIRST NATIONS, of 15,080.384 hectares (37,264.29 acres), including mines and minerals, as an addition to Salt River First Nation Indian Reserve No. 195, and; 3) repealing Order in Council P.C. 2009-1244 of July 30, 2009, as the French version of the Schedule II is incorrect.
